<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-54-1274 </DOCNO><TEXT>The connection to the grid of an industrial combined heat and power plantis described. During the construction of the new plant gradual dismantlementand restructuring of the existing plant should take place without interruptingthe power supply. This requires fine tuned control equipment which hasbeen designed by Akzo Engineering BV in cooperation with the electricutility EGD. In this part (part 2) attention is focussed on: demandsrelated to the connection to the public grid, main switch station, fireprevention measures, idle power control, 66 kV synchronization equipment,and operation of the plant. 4 figs., 3 refs.</TEXT></DOC>